Medior Professional, Young Professional

Our Digital Manufacturing division, with over 200 colleagues, supports partners with their digital transformation journeys. We work on Industry 4.0 topics and add value by enhancing efficiency and sustainability.

Jouw job in één alinea

Nikos Pantazopoulos and Alexander van Berne, Unit Managers - Intelligent Automation:
"As Industry 4.0 / Connectivity Consultant in our team, you will be working in complex projects for our clients in various industries such as Life Sciences, Food and Beverage, Manufacturing and Logistics. Together we overcome challenges around digital transformation within the IT/OT domain. You will advise, design, and implement process improvements in the field of Industrial Automation. We are making use of cutting-edge technologies in the fields of IIoT, Edge computing, data engineering, artificial intelligence etc. A challenging role, where we are looking for individuals who like being part of interdisciplinary teams and enjoys travelling (internationally) to factory sites when needed. If you loved ‘How it’s made’ on Discovery Channel then we are sure you would fit right in."
In short:
Acting as system integrator by installing and configuring solutions and implementing connections to brownfield equipment;
Consulting about solutions for IT/OT integration, getting data from machines;
Collaborating with clients and vendors to map the ‘as is’ situation and design a strategy toward connecting factories and equipment;
Having career perspective toward designing Cloud Infrastructures, Data Analytics and Artificial Intelligence.
Je thuisbasis bij Capgemini

Within Digital Manufacturing, you will be part of a group offering tailored Industry 4.0 solutions. We support clients with creating smart factories. Our colleagues have extensive knowledge of IoT, Connectivity, Artificial Intelligence, Automation programs and Validation. With this knowledge we operate in various industries, including Life Sciences, Infrastructure, Energy and Manufacturing. Do you find it interesting to know how quality and compliance requirements are met around COVID-19, or how Digital Twins support an Industry 4.0 architecture for Bluetooth devices? Then we recommend to apply here!

Benefits
A permanent contract and an attractive salary;
Our Academy, where you can follow meaningful trainings and courses;
Holiday pay and plenty of time (26 days) to spend it. You could even buy more days;
A non-contributory pension scheme, so you’ll be looking back fondly at your time at Capgemini Engineering;
Work where you like on a device of your choice and our connectivity allowance;
Your first necessity of life as a Capgemini Engineering professional: a fast laptop and a SIM card that you can also use privately.

Waarom past deze vacature bij jou?
You have experience with connectivity between level 1-2 and 3 systems (e.g. KEPware, Historians);
You have strong knowledge about PLC/SCADA and communication protocols (e.g. Modbus, OPC-UA, MQTT);
You have knowledge about network infrastructure (LAN);
You have an educational background in Industrial Automation, Electrical Engineering or Data Science within manufacturing.
